Senior Project Manager
03 May 2014 06:44 AM - UAE
.
The Senior Project Manager role is accountable for the project management, operational performance, technical and people leadership of large scale multi disciplinary project or smaller simulataneous projects across WSP Middle East (ME). The role holder must take a 'hands on' approach to all aspects of the role.
Responsibilities
Project Leadership • Lead and project manage successful delivery of large scale or smaller simultaneous multi disciplinary projects in line with the Project Lifecycle.• Support the formation of the contractual relationship between the business and the client; taking the process from proposal to contract, utilising the advice of the support functions• Engage with the CRCs at the Prospect stage through to completion to ensure the most cost efficient delivery of their projects.• Ensure proactive project planning, stakeholder and risk management takes place across projects• Supervise the team to identify, assess and manage major project risk and secure the best commercial return from the projects in their portfolio• Establish, monitor and maintain a schedule of forecast resources required to deliver the project. Check the resources against the fee to ensure they balance• Regularly review resource usage against the schedule and take corrective action where required• Establish, monitor and maintain a schedule of project reviews and track any corrective actions and ensure they are properly closed out• To ensure statutory and regulatory requirements are met• Responsible for the delivery of project P&L budgets, forecasts and working capital targets for own projects and projects led by direct reports• Responsible for the accurate and timely recognition of revenue for projects • Support the overseeing and delivery of the process of working capital management from inception to completion within set deadlines; This includes the timing of invoicing, the review of Work in Progress (WIP) and the collection of outstanding invoices from clients whilst utilising the advice of the support functions as necessary• Contribute to the completion of monthly management project reports to be issued by set deadlineBusiness Leadership• Responsible for the leadership and support of their team• Ensure that Health & Safety is embedded into all work practices in line with company policies• Ensure the right resources are utilised effectively at the right time across their team and projects. Including engaging with the Complimentary Resource Centres (CRCs) to ensure that communication and design processes are continually improved• Input into the recruitment and selection process• Contribute to meaningful inductions, performance management reviews and personal development plans that support the development of individuals and the business• Contribute to succession planning and career development across their team• Support the development and delivery of training and awareness sessions as required• Contribute to the development and implementation of the business unit (BU) strategy• Attend and lead team and project meetings, cascade relevant information and encourage feedback from team• Input into setting and delivering P&L BU budget and forecasts• Lead by example and ensure QMS and Project Lifecycle compliance across projects.• Provide guidance and support the companies approach to Sustainability and ensure that the Sustainability strategy is implemented across projectsBusiness Development• Contribute to business development activities through participation in external market profile raising activities and functions• Actively develop external and internal client relationships• Proactively co sell other WSP ME services and where applicable the wider business• Contribute to the Key Account Management (KAM) programmes, with the aim of increasing client intelligence to develop win solutions and support unique selling points for prospects.• Support the 'Prospect to Project Process' for lead projects and overseeing the process for direct reports • Act as Prospect Manager on selected projects• Provide technical leadership to respond to prequalification documents, Request for Price (RFPs) and other client inquiries• Contribute to the financial build-up of resources and lump sum pricing items for prospects where requiredTechnical• Provide support and guidance to Technical Working Group (TWG)• Keep up to date with industry developments with respect to own discipline and understand and appreciate the basic technical principles and drivers of other disciplines• Develop the project management capabilities of the project team• Facilitate technical solutions on projects• Provide support and guidance to Technical Working Group (TWG)• Contribute to and lead design peer reviews in alignment with the QMS system
Requirements
• BEng /BSc (Hon) degree or equivalent discipline with minimum 10 years post graduate experience• Member of associated Professional body • NA preferred although not essential• Experience and proven ability to lead and manage an engineering team and multi-disciplinary projects• Experiences user of Microsoft Office• Comprehensive experience of technic (more...)
